{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_JiNDkE3z9WMt4mU4zUxDRwpi","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/**\n2\t * STATEMENT_PROTOCOL — the single source of the statement-emission rules that\n3\t * every lmthing VM context (top-level session, fork leaf, delegate) puts at the\n4\t * top of its system prompt.\n5\t *\n6\t * Before exec unification these rules were paraphrased in three places that\n7\t * drifted apart: `context/system-block.ts` RUNTIME_PREAMBLE (session +\n8\t * delegate), the fork system-prompt builder in `fork/fork.ts`, and the SCOPE\n9\t * paragraph of `fork/roles.ts` FIREWALL_TAIL — plus the canonical prose in\n10\t * the system-space authoring notes (now org/docs/system-spaces/README.md). The\n11\t * harness now injects this string ONCE\n12\t * per context (via `buildSystemBlock` for session/delegate and the fork\n13\t * builder); role preambles and context-specific sections add only what is\n14\t * genuinely context-specific.\n15\t *\n16\t * IMPORTANT: this text is part of every system prompt, so it must stay free of\n17\t * markers that scripted-mock rules key on to distinguish contexts (e.g.\n18\t * \"currentTask\", \"ROLE:\", \"Run action:\").\n19\t */\n20\texport const STATEMENT_PROTOCOL = `\n21\tCRITICAL INSTRUCTION: You are a TypeScript code execution agent. Your entire response is fed directly into a TypeScript evaluator, so it MUST be valid TypeScript. Do NOT emit bare prose, explanations, JSON, markdown, or natural language — a single word of non-code, non-comment text is a typecheck error that wastes a turn.\n22\t\n23\tIf you want to think out loud, explain your reasoning, or narrate a plan, write it INSIDE a \\`// comment\\`. Comments are valid TypeScript and are encouraged for narration — bare sentences are not. Example:\n24\t  // First load the knowledge, then diagnose from the user's query.\n25\t  const k = await loadKnowledge(\"espresso\", \"fundamentals\", \"overview.md\");\n26\t\n27\tRespond with valid TypeScript statements only. Use top-level \\`await\\` for async operations. Do not wrap code in functions or markdown code blocks. Just write the statements directly.\n28\t\n29\tABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN — these will cause parse errors or runtime errors:\n30\t  - \\`\\`\\`typescript or \\`\\`\\`ts or \\`\\`\\` (markdown code fences of any kind)\n31\t  - Bare English text or explanations OUTSIDE of a \\`//\\` comment\n32\t  - function wrappers, IIFE patterns, or async IIFEs like \\`await (async () => { ... })()\\`\n33\t  - setTimeout, setInterval, clearTimeout, clearInterval, queueMicrotask (not available — use sleep() instead)\n34\t\n35\tUse sequential top-level await statements, not IIFEs:\n36\tWRONG: const x = await (async () => { const t = await doWork(); return t; })()\n37\tCORRECT: const x = await doWork();\n38\t\n39\tSTATEMENT SHAPE — statements are evaluated ONE AT A TIME:\n40\t  - Keep value-yielding calls FLAT at top level — never inside if/try/catch/loop bodies or nested callbacks (code after a nested yield is lost when the turn resumes). Guard with a ternary instead: \\`const detail = needDetail ? await fetch(url) : undefined;\\`\n41\t  - Declare a variable and use it in the same statement where possible; never split a \\`let\\`/\\`const\\` declaration from its first use across separate statements. If a binding errored, re-bind it before reusing the name.\n42\t`.trim();\n43\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4bfa69d9-de98-4976-b4ad-12c5314f8543","uuid":"55b7bb71-7be2-48b0-83ed-b66cfc88dbf0","timestamp":"2026-07-14T17:16:43.071Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/exec/preamble.ts","content":"/**\n * STATEMENT_PROTOCOL — the single source of the statement-emission rules that\n * every lmthing VM context (top-level session, fork leaf, delegate) puts at the\n * top of its system prompt.\n *\n * Before exec unification these rules were paraphrased in three places that\n * drifted apart: `context/system-block.ts` RUNTIME_PREAMBLE (session +\n * delegate), the fork system-prompt builder in `fork/fork.ts`, and the SCOPE\n * paragraph of `fork/roles.ts` FIREWALL_TAIL — plus the canonical prose in\n * the system-space authoring notes (now org/docs/system-spaces/README.md). The\n * harness now injects this string ONCE\n * per context (via `buildSystemBlock` for session/delegate and the fork\n * builder); role preambles and context-specific sections add only what is\n * genuinely context-specific.\n *\n * IMPORTANT: this text is part of every system prompt, so it must stay free of\n * markers that scripted-mock rules key on to distinguish contexts (e.g.\n * \"currentTask\", \"ROLE:\", \"Run action:\").\n */\nexport const STATEMENT_PROTOCOL = `\nCRITICAL INSTRUCTION: You are a TypeScript code execution agent. Your entire response is fed directly into a TypeScript evaluator, so it MUST be valid TypeScript. Do NOT emit bare prose, explanations, JSON, markdown, or natural language — a single word of non-code, non-comment text is a typecheck error that wastes a turn.\n\nIf you want to think out loud, explain your reasoning, or narrate a plan, write it INSIDE a \\`// comment\\`. Comments are valid TypeScript and are encouraged for narration — bare sentences are not. Example:\n  // First load the knowledge, then diagnose from the user's query.\n  const k = await loadKnowledge(\"espresso\", \"fundamentals\", \"overview.md\");\n\nRespond with valid TypeScript statements only. Use top-level \\`await\\` for async operations. Do not wrap code in functions or markdown code blocks. Just write the statements directly.\n\nABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN — these will cause parse errors or runtime errors:\n  - \\`\\`\\`typescript or \\`\\`\\`ts or \\`\\`\\` (markdown code fences of any kind)\n  - Bare English text or explanations OUTSIDE of a \\`//\\` comment\n  - function wrappers, IIFE patterns, or async IIFEs like \\`await (async () => { ... })()\\`\n  - setTimeout, setInterval, clearTimeout, clearInterval, queueMicrotask (not available — use sleep() instead)\n\nUse sequential top-level await statements, not IIFEs:\nWRONG: const x = await (async () => { const t = await doWork(); return t; })()\nCORRECT: const x = await doWork();\n\nSTATEMENT SHAPE — statements are evaluated ONE AT A TIME:\n  - Keep value-yielding calls FLAT at top level — never inside if/try/catch/loop bodies or nested callbacks (code after a nested yield is lost when the turn resumes). Guard with a ternary instead: \\`const detail = needDetail ? await fetch(url) : undefined;\\`\n  - Declare a variable and use it in the same statement where possible; never split a \\`let\\`/\\`const\\` declaration from its first use across separate statements. If a binding errored, re-bind it before reusing the name.\n`.trim();\n","numLines":43,"startLine":1,"totalLines":43}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_3cr9XnUme4f1T0TXuRMYnvXH","type":"tool_result","content":"130\t  private currentScope: TraceScope | null = null;\n131\t  /** Counter for run nodes (start/continue/resume calls). */\n132\t  private runCount = 0;\n133\t  /**\n134\t   * One ForkEngine per session, lazily built and reused across fork/tasklist\n135\t   * yields so the maxConcurrentForks semaphore is enforced across ALL top-level\n136\t   * fork() yields — not just within a single Promise.all batch. Reset on\n137\t   * start()/resume() when agent functions change.\n138\t   */\n139\t  private forkEngine: import('../fork/fork.js').ForkEngine | null = null;\n140\t  /**\n141\t   * Host-enforced budget for the current turn-loop run. Reset per\n142\t   * start()/continue() so each task gets a fresh ceiling. The `progress` global\n143\t   * reads this live (the closure dereferences the field, so resetting works).\n144\t   */\n145\t  private budget: Budget = new Budget();\n146\t  /**\n147\t   * Accumulated statement context (typecheck scope) carried ACROSS turns. The VM\n148\t   * keeps every variable a turn binds, but each runTurnLoop starts with an empty\n149\t   * typecheck scope — so without this, a continue()/resume() turn that references\n150\t   * a variable bound in an earlier turn fails tsc with \"Cannot find name\". Seeded\n151\t   * into runTurnLoop as initialContext and updated via onContextSnapshot. Reset to\n152\t   * '' by start() (a fresh program); preserved by continue()/resume().\n153\t   */\n154\t  private turnContext = '';\n155\t\n156\t  constructor(opts: SessionOpts, deps: SessionDeps) {\n157\t    this.opts = opts;\n158\t    this.deps = deps;\n159\t    this.history = new MessageHistory();\n160\t    this.sessionId = randomUUID();\n161\t    this.tracer = new Tracer(opts.traceFile ?? null);\n162\t  }\n163\t\n164\t  /** Expose the tracer so the CLI can subscribe the TraceHub to it. */\n165\t  getTracer(): Tracer { return this.tracer; }\n166\t\n167\t  /** The root execution-node id for this session (the `session_start` nodeId).\n168\t   *  Used by hosts to attribute node-less events (e.g. an injected user_message)\n169\t   *  to the session root instead of falling back to a phantom node. */\n170\t  getRootNodeId(): string { return this.sessionId; }\n171\t\n172\t  /** The full message history (for persisting a resumable session snapshot). */\n173\t  getHistory(): import('../context/history.js').Message[] { return this.history.messages; }\n174\t\n175\t  /** Ingest a user turn: record this turn's image/file attachments into\n176\t   *  `pendingAttachments` (for id-based delegation) and return the text to append\n177\t   *  to history — the user's text, optionally framed, plus a note listing THIS\n178\t   *  turn's attachments by id. The raw bytes are NOT put on the text agent's message.\n179\t   *\n180\t   *  Attachments ACCUMULATE across the session's turns — they are NOT cleared each\n181\t   *  turn. THING's propose→consent→build flow spans two turns (turn 1: the user\n182\t   *  dumps files and THING offers; turn 2: a bare \"yes please\" and THING builds),\n183\t   *  so the automator delegate that seeds the app fires a turn AFTER the files\n184\t   *  arrived. Clearing on every turn made turn 1's upload ids unresolvable by turn 2\n185\t   *  (`runDelegate` → `pendingAttachments.get(id)` → undefined), so THING handed the\n186\t   *  automator a placeholder id, `readDocument` read nothing, and the app's budget\n187\t   *  tables were created EMPTY. Upload ids are unique and an attachment ref is cheap\n188\t   *  metadata (id + mediaType + url, no bytes), so keeping every id the session has\n189\t   *  seen addressable is safe and is what makes cross-turn \"here's a file … now use\n190\t   *  it\" work at all. The note still lists only the CURRENT turn's attachments, so\n191\t   *  the agent isn't re-told about old ones each turn. */\n192\t  private ingestUserTurn(message: UserInput, opts?: { frame?: boolean }): string {\n193\t    const { text, attachments } = normalizeInput(message);\n194\t    const atts = attachments ?? [];\n195\t    for (const a of atts) this.pendingAttachments.set(a.id, a);\n196\t    const framed = opts?.frame === false ? text : `User request:\\n\\n${text}`;\n197\t    return framed + attachmentNote(atts);\n198\t  }\n199\t\n200\t  async continue(message: UserInput): Promise<void> {\n201\t    if (!this.vm || !this.systemBlock || !this.ambientDts) {\n202\t      throw new Error('Session not started — call start() first');\n203\t    }\n204\t    // Neutral framing: the TS-statement reply channel is fully specified by\n205\t    // STATEMENT_PROTOCOL in the system block. Framing the user's message itself as\n206\t    // \"write TypeScript code\" primed the triage toward the code path for EVERY\n207\t    // request (live E3 regression: a deep-research ask routed to the engineer).\n208\t    this.history.append({\n209\t      role: 'user',\n210\t      content: this.ingestUserTurn(message),\n211\t      blockType: 'normal',\n212\t    });\n213\t    // Context economy: collapse old turns into a summary once history grows large,\n214\t    // keeping the most recent messages (incl. this task) verbatim.\n215\t    await this.maybeSummarizeHistory();\n216\t    this.budget = new Budget(this.opts.budget ?? {});\n217\t    const runScope = this.mintRunScope();\n218\t    try {\n219\t      await runTurnLoop({\n220\t        vm: this.vm,\n221\t        history: this.history,\n222\t        systemBlock: this.systemBlock,\n223\t        ambientDts: this.ambientDts,\n224\t        renderHost: this.opts.renderHost,\n225\t        streamFn: this.deps.streamFn,\n226\t        processYield: (req) => this.handleYield(req),\n227\t        maxRetries: this.opts.maxRetries,\n228\t        tracer: this.tracer,\n229\t        traceContext: 'session',\n230\t        scope: runScope,\n231\t        budget: this.budget,\n232\t        initialContext: this.turnContext,\n233\t        onContextSnapshot: (c) => { this.turnContext = c; },\n234\t        model: this.opts.modelAlias,\n235\t        beforeTurn: () => this.readTodoReminder(),\n236\t        streamIdleMs: this.opts.streamIdleMs,\n237\t      });\n238\t      this.tracer.end(runScope, 'done');\n239\t    } catch (err) {\n240\t      this.tracer.end(runScope, 'error', { error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err) });\n241\t      throw err;\n242\t    }\n243\t  }\n244\t\n245\t  async start(initialMessage: UserInput): Promise<void> {\n246\t    // 1. Load space + merge always-on system spaces\n247\t    this.space = await this.loadMergedSpace(this.opts.spaceDir);\n248\t\n249\t    // 1b. Preload any project spaces into dynamicSpaces so they are delegatable immediately.\n250\t    // Failures are isolated — one bad dir must not abort startup.\n251\t    for (const dir of this.opts.preloadSpaceDirs ?? []) {\n252\t      try {\n253\t        const preloadedSpace = await loadSpace(dir);\n254\t        this.dynamicSpaces.set(dir, preloadedSpace);\n255\t      } catch (err) {\n256\t        this.opts.renderHost.log(`[warn] preloadSpaceDirs: failed to load space at \"${dir}\": ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`);\n257\t      }\n258\t    }\n259\t\n260\t    // 2. Get agent — fall back to first agent when slug is 'default'\n261\t    const agentKeys = Object.keys(this.space.agents);\n262\t    const resolvedSlug = this.opts.agentSlug === 'default' && !this.space.agents['default']\n263\t      ? agentKeys[0]\n264\t      : this.opts.agentSlug;\n265\t    if (!resolvedSlug) {\n266\t      throw new Error(`No agents found in space at \"${this.opts.spaceDir}\"`);\n267\t    }\n268\t    const agent = this.space.agents[resolvedSlug];\n269\t    if (!agent) {\n270\t      throw new Error(`Agent \"${this.opts.agentSlug}\" not found in space at \"${this.opts.spaceDir}\"`);\n271\t    }\n272\t\n273\t    // 3. Resolve direct dependencies + the unified canDelegateTo policy (gates\n274\t    // whether `delegate` is injected/declared AND which targets a yield may hit).\n275\t    this.delegatePolicy = evaluateDelegatePolicy(agent.canDelegateTo, 'agent');\n276\t    const directDeps = resolveDirectDeps(this.space, agent.canDelegateTo);\n277\t\n278\t    // 4. Build system block (system functions rendered as a concise Built-in Tools list)\n279\t    const systemFns = systemFunctionSources(this.systemSpaces);\n280\t    const knowledgePreloads = await resolvePreloadedKnowledge(this.space, agent);\n281\t    const systemBlock = buildSystemBlock({ space: this.space, agent, directDeps, systemFunctions: systemFns, knowledgePreloads, omitDelegate: this.delegatePolicy.mode === 'none' }) + this.projectAgentsBlock();\n282\t\n283\t    // 4b. Build ambient DTS overlay — system functions are always in scope, then agent functions\n284\t    const { functions: agentFunctions, functionsBundled: agentFunctionsBundled } =\n285\t      this.buildInjectedFunctions(this.space, agent);\n286\t    const agentComponents = getAgentComponents(this.space, agent);\n287\t    const overlay = buildOverlay(agentFunctions, agentComponents, (name, message) => {\n288\t      this.opts.renderHost.log(`[warn] ${name}: ${message}`);\n289\t    });\n290\t    this.appCapabilities = agent.capabilities ?? {};\n291\t    const ambientDts = buildAmbientDts({ capabilities: sessionCapabilities(this.delegatePolicy.mode !== 'none', this.appCapabilities), overlay, appDts: this.opts.appDts, projectRoot: !!this.opts.projectRoot });\n292\t    this.systemBlock = systemBlock;\n293\t    this.ambientDts = ambientDts;\n294\t    this.agentFunctions = agentFunctions;\n295\t    this.agentFunctionsBundled = agentFunctionsBundled;\n296\t    this.forkEngine = null; // agent functions changed — rebuild on next fork yield\n297\t\n298\t    // 5. Create the VM via the shared bootstrap (functions, host tools, all\n299\t    // yielding globals incl. ask, JSX runtime with this agent's components).\n300\t    this.vm = await this.createSessionVM(agentFunctions, agentFunctionsBundled, [\n301\t      ...Object.keys(agentComponents.view),\n302\t      ...Object.keys(agentComponents.form),\n303\t    ]);\n304\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4bfa69d9-de98-4976-b4ad-12c5314f8543","uuid":"1c5ab930-a237-4099-be6f-523ad6b21663","timestamp":"2026-07-14T17:16:43.072Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/session/session.ts","content":"  private currentScope: TraceScope | null = null;\n  /** Counter for run nodes (start/continue/resume calls). */\n  private runCount = 0;\n  /**\n   * One ForkEngine per session, lazily built and reused across fork/tasklist\n   * yields so the maxConcurrentForks semaphore is enforced across ALL top-level\n   * fork() yields — not just within a single Promise.all batch. Reset on\n   * start()/resume() when agent functions change.\n   */\n  private forkEngine: import('../fork/fork.js').ForkEngine | null = null;\n  /**\n   * Host-enforced budget for the current turn-loop run. Reset per\n   * start()/continue() so each task gets a fresh ceiling. The `progress` global\n   * reads this live (the closure dereferences the field, so resetting works).\n   */\n  private budget: Budget = new Budget();\n  /**\n   * Accumulated statement context (typecheck scope) carried ACROSS turns. The VM\n   * keeps every variable a turn binds, but each runTurnLoop starts with an empty\n   * typecheck scope — so without this, a continue()/resume() turn that references\n   * a variable bound in an earlier turn fails tsc with \"Cannot find name\". Seeded\n   * into runTurnLoop as initialContext and updated via onContextSnapshot. Reset to\n   * '' by start() (a fresh program); preserved by continue()/resume().\n   */\n  private turnContext = '';\n\n  constructor(opts: SessionOpts, deps: SessionDeps) {\n    this.opts = opts;\n    this.deps = deps;\n    this.history = new MessageHistory();\n    this.sessionId = randomUUID();\n    this.tracer = new Tracer(opts.traceFile ?? null);\n  }\n\n  /** Expose the tracer so the CLI can subscribe the TraceHub to it. */\n  getTracer(): Tracer { return this.tracer; }\n\n  /** The root execution-node id for this session (the `session_start` nodeId).\n   *  Used by hosts to attribute node-less events (e.g. an injected user_message)\n   *  to the session root instead of falling back to a phantom node. */\n  getRootNodeId(): string { return this.sessionId; }\n\n  /** The full message history (for persisting a resumable session snapshot). */\n  getHistory(): import('../context/history.js').Message[] { return this.history.messages; }\n\n  /** Ingest a user turn: record this turn's image/file attachments into\n   *  `pendingAttachments` (for id-based delegation) and return the text to append\n   *  to history — the user's text, optionally framed, plus a note listing THIS\n   *  turn's attachments by id. The raw bytes are NOT put on the text agent's message.\n   *\n   *  Attachments ACCUMULATE across the session's turns — they are NOT cleared each\n   *  turn. THING's propose→consent→build flow spans two turns (turn 1: the user\n   *  dumps files and THING offers; turn 2: a bare \"yes please\" and THING builds),\n   *  so the automator delegate that seeds the app fires a turn AFTER the files\n   *  arrived. Clearing on every turn made turn 1's upload ids unresolvable by turn 2\n   *  (`runDelegate` → `pendingAttachments.get(id)` → undefined), so THING handed the\n   *  automator a placeholder id, `readDocument` read nothing, and the app's budget\n   *  tables were created EMPTY. Upload ids are unique and an attachment ref is cheap\n   *  metadata (id + mediaType + url, no bytes), so keeping every id the session has\n   *  seen addressable is safe and is what makes cross-turn \"here's a file … now use\n   *  it\" work at all. The note still lists only the CURRENT turn's attachments, so\n   *  the agent isn't re-told about old ones each turn. */\n  private ingestUserTurn(message: UserInput, opts?: { frame?: boolean }): string {\n    const { text, attachments } = normalizeInput(message);\n    const atts = attachments ?? [];\n    for (const a of atts) this.pendingAttachments.set(a.id, a);\n    const framed = opts?.frame === false ? text : `User request:\\n\\n${text}`;\n    return framed + attachmentNote(atts);\n  }\n\n  async continue(message: UserInput): Promise<void> {\n    if (!this.vm || !this.systemBlock || !this.ambientDts) {\n      throw new Error('Session not started — call start() first');\n    }\n    // Neutral framing: the TS-statement reply channel is fully specified by\n    // STATEMENT_PROTOCOL in the system block. Framing the user's message itself as\n    // \"write TypeScript code\" primed the triage toward the code path for EVERY\n    // request (live E3 regression: a deep-research ask routed to the engineer).\n    this.history.append({\n      role: 'user',\n      content: this.ingestUserTurn(message),\n      blockType: 'normal',\n    });\n    // Context economy: collapse old turns into a summary once history grows large,\n    // keeping the most recent messages (incl. this task) verbatim.\n    await this.maybeSummarizeHistory();\n    this.budget = new Budget(this.opts.budget ?? {});\n    const runScope = this.mintRunScope();\n    try {\n      await runTurnLoop({\n        vm: this.vm,\n        history: this.history,\n        systemBlock: this.systemBlock,\n        ambientDts: this.ambientDts,\n        renderHost: this.opts.renderHost,\n        streamFn: this.deps.streamFn,\n        processYield: (req) => this.handleYield(req),\n        maxRetries: this.opts.maxRetries,\n        tracer: this.tracer,\n        traceContext: 'session',\n        scope: runScope,\n        budget: this.budget,\n        initialContext: this.turnContext,\n        onContextSnapshot: (c) => { this.turnContext = c; },\n        model: this.opts.modelAlias,\n        beforeTurn: () => this.readTodoReminder(),\n        streamIdleMs: this.opts.streamIdleMs,\n      });\n      this.tracer.end(runScope, 'done');\n    } catch (err) {\n      this.tracer.end(runScope, 'error', { error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err) });\n      throw err;\n    }\n  }\n\n  async start(initialMessage: UserInput): Promise<void> {\n    // 1. Load space + merge always-on system spaces\n    this.space = await this.loadMergedSpace(this.opts.spaceDir);\n\n    // 1b. Preload any project spaces into dynamicSpaces so they are delegatable immediately.\n    // Failures are isolated — one bad dir must not abort startup.\n    for (const dir of this.opts.preloadSpaceDirs ?? []) {\n      try {\n        const preloadedSpace = await loadSpace(dir);\n        this.dynamicSpaces.set(dir, preloadedSpace);\n      } catch (err) {\n        this.opts.renderHost.log(`[warn] preloadSpaceDirs: failed to load space at \"${dir}\": ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 2. Get agent — fall back to first agent when slug is 'default'\n    const agentKeys = Object.keys(this.space.agents);\n    const resolvedSlug = this.opts.agentSlug === 'default' && !this.space.agents['default']\n      ? agentKeys[0]\n      : this.opts.agentSlug;\n    if (!resolvedSlug) {\n      throw new Error(`No agents found in space at \"${this.opts.spaceDir}\"`);\n    }\n    const agent = this.space.agents[resolvedSlug];\n    if (!agent) {\n      throw new Error(`Agent \"${this.opts.agentSlug}\" not found in space at \"${this.opts.spaceDir}\"`);\n    }\n\n    // 3. Resolve direct dependencies + the unified canDelegateTo policy (gates\n    // whether `delegate` is injected/declared AND which targets a yield may hit).\n    this.delegatePolicy = evaluateDelegatePolicy(agent.canDelegateTo, 'agent');\n    const directDeps = resolveDirectDeps(this.space, agent.canDelegateTo);\n\n    // 4. Build system block (system functions rendered as a concise Built-in Tools list)\n    const systemFns = systemFunctionSources(this.systemSpaces);\n    const knowledgePreloads = await resolvePreloadedKnowledge(this.space, agent);\n    const systemBlock = buildSystemBlock({ space: this.space, agent, directDeps, systemFunctions: systemFns, knowledgePreloads, omitDelegate: this.delegatePolicy.mode === 'none' }) + this.projectAgentsBlock();\n\n    // 4b. Build ambient DTS overlay — system functions are always in scope, then agent functions\n    const { functions: agentFunctions, functionsBundled: agentFunctionsBundled } =\n      this.buildInjectedFunctions(this.space, agent);\n    const agentComponents = getAgentComponents(this.space, agent);\n    const overlay = buildOverlay(agentFunctions, agentComponents, (name, message) => {\n      this.opts.renderHost.log(`[warn] ${name}: ${message}`);\n    });\n    this.appCapabilities = agent.capabilities ?? {};\n    const ambientDts = buildAmbientDts({ capabilities: sessionCapabilities(this.delegatePolicy.mode !== 'none', this.appCapabilities), overlay, appDts: this.opts.appDts, projectRoot: !!this.opts.projectRoot });\n    this.systemBlock = systemBlock;\n    this.ambientDts = ambientDts;\n    this.agentFunctions = agentFunctions;\n    this.agentFunctionsBundled = agentFunctionsBundled;\n    this.forkEngine = null; // agent functions changed — rebuild on next fork yield\n\n    // 5. Create the VM via the shared bootstrap (functions, host tools, all\n    // yielding globals incl. ask, JSX runtime with this agent's components).\n    this.vm = await this.createSessionVM(agentFunctions, agentFunctionsBundled, [\n      ...Object.keys(agentComponents.view),\n      ...Object.keys(agentComponents.form),\n    ]);\n","numLines":175,"startLine":130,"totalLines":1004}}}
