sd\": 87\n        }\n      ],\n      \"totalLodgingCost\": 2151\n    },\n    \"costs\": {\n      \"flightsEur\": 2707,\n      \"safari\": {\n        \"total\": 1200,\n        \"depositPaid\": 240,\n        \"balanceDueOnArrival\": 960\n      },\n      \"dining\": {\n        \"rockRestaurantZanzibar\": 46\n      },\n      \"transport\": {\n        \"zanzibarLocalDrivingPermit\": 15\n      },\n      \"visa\": {\n        \"tanzaniaEVisa\": 100,\n        \"egyptEVisa\": 130,\n        \"total\": 230\n      },\n      \"insurance\": {\n        \"zanzibarMandatoryInsurance\": 88\n      },\n      \"parkFees\": {\n        \"ngorongoroEntryPermit_2pax_nonEA_adult\": 141.6,\n        \"ngorongoroCraterServiceFee_2pax_nonEA_adult\": 141.6,\n        \"ngorongoroCraterVehicleDescentFee_perVehicle_nonEA\": 295,\n        \"tarangireNpEntrance_2pax_peak\": 118,\n        \"lakeManyaraNpEntrance_2pax_peak\": 118,\n        \"totalParkFees\": 814.2\n      },\n      \"lodgingTotal_exclSafariPackage\": 951,\n      \"totalUsd_exclFlights\": 3344.2\n    },\n    \"notes\": \"Flights are in EUR (€2,707); everything else is in USD. The legs sheet lodging total ($2,151) includes the safari package ($1,200); the costs sheet lodging total ($951) excludes it. The costs sheet grand total is $3,344.20 USD (excluding EUR flights). Combined trip cost: €2,707 + $3,344.20 USD.\"\n  }\n}\n{\n  \"type\": \"yield_resolved\",\n  \"kind\": \"delegate\",\n  \"value\": \"SUMMARY OF ALL THREE DOCUMENTS\\n==============================\\n\\nDOCUMENT 1: tanzaniamemories.md (Markdown notes — Trip Plan)\\n=============================================================\\n\\nPURPOSE & TRAVELERS\\n- Vasileios Kefallinos + Athina Mari, fully booked trip Aug 3–20, 2026.\\n- Route: Cairo → Arusha → northern Tanzania safari circuit → Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam → Cairo.\\n- All flights, accommodations, safari, and key dining confirmed.\\n\\nFULL FLIGHT ITINERARY (6 legs, ~€2,707 total for both travelers):\\n- Aug 3: ATH→CAI, Aegean A3932, 06:55–08:50, ref ZZJQUU\\n- Aug 4: CAI→DAR, EgyptAir, 22:40–04:20+1 (overnight)\\n- Aug 5: DAR→ARK, Precision Air TC144, 10:50–12:00\\n- Aug 11: ARK→ZNZ, Precision Air TC145, 12:40–13:40\\n- Aug 19: DAR→CAI, EgyptAir, 05:20–11:05\\n- Aug 20: CAI→ATH, Aegean A3935, 19:55–22:00, ref ZZL22S\\n- Precision Air flights have luggage restrictions favoring soft bags.\\n\\nACCOMMODATIONS (every night accounted for, 17 nights total):\\n- Eileen Hotel, Cairo — Aug 3–5 (2 nights), 21 Youssef El-Gendy St, Downtown Cairo, near Tahrir Square\\n- Serengeti Villa, Arusha — Aug 5–7 (2 nights), +255 757 757 928\\n- Safari Aug 7–9: Twiga Camp Site (Tarangire, FB) → Twiga Camp Site (Lake Manyara, FB) → Jevas Hotel (Ngorongoro, HB)\\n- Kutoka Lodge, Arusha — Aug 9–11 (2 nights)\\n- Treasures of Zanzibar House, Stone Town — Aug 11–13 (2 nights)\\n- Ayla Beach House, Kiwengwa, Zanzibar — Aug 13–17 (4 nights)\\n- Sunny Shore B&B, Dar es Salaam — Aug 17–19 (2 nights)\\n- Ramses Hilton, Cairo — Aug 19–20 (1 night)\\n\\nSAFARI (Suricata Safaris Ltd):\\n- 3-day group camping safari, Aug 7–9.\\n- Tarangire NP → Lake Manyara NP → Ngorongoro Crater.\\n- Contact: Richard, +255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com\\n- Cost: $1,200 total for 2 pax. $240 deposit paid (20%). $960 balance due on arrival.\\n- Payment: cash (USD post-2009 notes) or Pesapal online (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris\\n- Ngorongoro nights are cold — warm layers essential.\\n- August is peak season with Great Wildebeest Migration.\\n\\nDINING:\\n- The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00, 2 adults. Fully paid ($46). Outdoor seating requested.\\n- 2x Tropical Passion Fruit Cheesecake included.\\n- Contact: +255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com\\n\\nCAIRO SIGHTSEEING:\\n- Stopover 1 (Aug 3–4): Grand Egyptian Museum, Pyramids of Giza. Eileen Hotel base.\\n- Stopover 2 (Aug 19–20): Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, Coptic Cairo. Ramses Hilton base.\\n\\nZANZIBAR:\\n- Driving: IDP + local Zanzibar Driving Permit (~$15, valid up to 3 months). Carry both; police checkpoints frequent.\\n- Swimming: north coast (Nungwi area) best; east/south coast limited by low tide.\\n- Ferry to Dar es Salaam.\\n\\nDAR ES SALAAM (by ferry from Zanzibar):\\n- Kivukoni Fish Market, Kariakoo Market, National Museum, Coco Beach, Bongoyo Island.\\n\\nVISA & INSURANCE REQUIREMENTS:\\n- Tanzania e-visa: mandatory online, $50/person at visa.immigration.go.tz (visa-on-arrival abolished Jan 2025).\\n- Egypt e-visa: multiple-entry, $65/person. Printed copy mandatory.\\n- Zanzibar: mandatory separate travel insurance from Zanzibar Insurance Corporation ($44/person).\\n\\nKEY PRINCIPLES:\\n- EgyptAir confirmed for Cairo↔Dar legs.\\n- Vasilis uses Greek & English interchangeably; prefers bullet lists unless table requested.\\n- Decathlon Forclaz trekking line recommended for safari gear; DEET insect repellent essential.\\n\\n\\nDOCUMENT 2: ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf (Ngorongoro Conservation Area Authority Tariffs)\\n========================================================================================================\\n\\nAll amounts for Non-East African Citizens (applicable to Vasilis & Athina) unless noted:\\n\\nENTRY PERMIT (valid 24 hours, single entry):\\n- Adults (16+ years): $70.80/person\\n- Children 5–16 years: $23.60/person\\n- Children under 5: Free\\n\\nCRATER SERVICE FEE (single entry):\\n- Adults: $70.80/person (public campsite rate)\\n- Children 5–16: $35.40\\n- Children under 5: Free\\n\\nPUBLIC CAMPSITE (non-EA):\\n- Adults: $70.80/person\\n- Children 5–16: $35.40\\n- Children under 5: Free\\n\\nSPECIAL CAMPSITE (non-EA):\\n- Adults: $59.00/person\\n- Children 5–16: $11.80\\n- Children under 5: Free\\n\\nMOTOR VEHICLE PERMIT (foreign registered, per vehicle):\\n- Up to 2000kg tare weight: $47.20\\n- 2001–3000kg: $177.00\\n- 3001–7000kg: $236.00\\n- 7001kg and above: $354.00\\n- Only 4x4 vehicles up to 3,500kg tare weight allowed on crater floor.\\n\\nCAMPING FEES (non-EA):\\n- Adults: $35.40/person\\n- Children 5–16: $11.80\\n- Children under 5: Free\\n\\nCULTURAL BOMAS ENTRY: $20.00/vehicle (non-EA).\\n\\nWALKING SAFARI GUIDE FEES (non-EA):\\n- Short walks (1–4 hours): $23.60/adult, $11.80/child\\n- Long walks (above 4 hours): $29.50/adult, $17.70/child\\n- Endoro Nature Trail & Elephant Caves: $17.70/adult, $11.80/child\\n\\nHOT AIR BALLOON SAFARIS (non-EA):\\n- Adults (16+): $59.00\n{\n  \"type\": \"variables\",\n  \"vars\": {\n    \"readerAnswer\": \"\\\"SUMMARY OF ALL THREE DOCUMENTS\\\\n==============================\\\\n\\\\nDOCUMENT 1: tanzaniamemories.md (Markdown notes — Trip Plan)\\\\n=============================================================\\\\n\\\\nPURPOSE & TRA… (8348 chars total)\\\"\",\n    \"sheetAnswer\": \"{\\\"legs\\\": {\\\"rowCount\\\": 8, \\\"totalNights\\\": 17, \\\"rows\\\": [{\\\"leg\\\": \\\"Cairo (arrival stopover)\\\", \\\"dates\\\": \\\"Aug 3-5\\\", \\\"nights\\\": 2, \\\"lodging\\\": \\\"Eileen Hotel\\\", \\\"costUsd\\\": 102}, {\\\"leg\\\": \\\"Arusha (pre-safari)\\\", \\\"dates\\\": \\\"Aug 5-7\\\", \\\"nights\\\": 2, \\\"lodging\\\": \\\"Serengeti Villa\\\", \\\"costUsd\\\": 62}, {\\\"leg\\\": \\\"Safari circuit - Tarangire / Lake Manyara / Ngorongoro Crater\\\", \\\"dates\\\": \\\"Aug 7-9\\\", \\\"nights\\\": 2, \\\"lodging\\\": \\\"Suricata Safaris (Twiga camps + Jevas Hotel, package)\\\", \\\"costUsd\\\": 1200}, {\\\"leg\\\": \\\"Arusha (post-safari)\\\", \\\"dates\\\": \\\"Aug 9-11\\\", \\\"nights\\\": 2, \\\"lodging\\\": \\\"Kutoka Lodge\\\", \\\"costUsd\\\": 96}, {\\\"leg\\\": \\\"Zanzibar - Stone Town\\\", \\\"dates\\\": \\\"Aug 11-13\\\", \\\"nights\\\": 2, \\\"lodging\\\": \\\"Treasures of Zanzibar House\\\", \\\"costUsd\\\": 100}, {\\\"leg\\\": \\\"Zanzibar - beach (Kiwengwa)\\\", \\\"dates\\\": \\\"Aug 13-17\\\", \\\"nights\\\": 4, \\\"lodging\\\": \\\"Ayla Beach House\\\", \\\"costUsd\\\": 304}, {\\\"leg\\\":